tip.text: Don't get the hype about this place actually. Authentic? Actually, I don't think so... The service was great though! Order got lost in system so they gave us free corn tea as service recovery🤔
這裡的玫瑰花園紅絲絨蛋糕好好吃！繽紛雙果園酸酸甜甜的，很開胃又好喝😍 Try their Red Velvet Cake and Orange and Passion Fruit Milk Drink! Tart and refreshing! Would love to try their food next time I'm back in Taiwan!😋

formattedAddress: 羅斯福路三段316巷9弄7號 (汀州路三段)

tip.text: 來這裡參觀展覽喔～ 2015年冬天時來參觀蛋黃哥的展覽的！A lot of exhibitions on display here. Come and see what's on display. You might just be surprised by the interesting exhibitions here. We went for Gudetama's exhibition!🍳

venue.name: National Taiwan Science Education Center (國立臺灣科學教育館 National Taiwan Science Education Center)

tip.text: 喜歡這裡的氣氛。本身覺得食物不怎麼夠味⋯ 但酥脆又有嚼勁的叉燒（不是廣式的喔）是一級棒。大愛！😍😋 來嚐嚐似乎真宗的台灣美食吧！Love the simplicity here. Feel that the food here are not flavourful enough for my taste...
漂亮、古典又宜人的裝潢⋯ 彷彿穿越時空，只為了一杯咖啡！樓上有較多座位，上樓看看吧！真想賴在這裡不走。😆 This Starbucks is located in an old but beautiful building. You will feel like you've travelled through time, just for a cuppa. Enjoy!😉
與大自然親近～ 這裡的空氣很清新！這裡的許願樹好可愛（可以在卡片上寫下願望喔）！餐館的食物也很好吃。😋 入門時付的入門費會轉化為購物/餐券供參觀者使用喔～ Abundant fresh air as it's in the countryside. Make a wish at the wishing tree, have a good meal at their restaurant!👍🏻
遲來的評語！2015年冬季時光顧的。芒果冰磚好好吃！但三個女生都吃不完⋯ 份量很大喔～ 另一點是這裡的裝潢很特別！！👍🏻 The Mango "Shaved Ice" is good! Portion is huge, and 3 of us (all girls) weren't able to finish it! Very cool interior and crowded!

venue.name: 台中市第四信用合作社

tip.text: 遲來了的評語。2015年冬天來光顧的。很喜歡這裡的氣氛與服務！能靜靜的喝著抹茶歐蕾，吃著冬季限定的草莓鬆餅。簡單，但好幸福！這裡有著純樸的感覺，少了城市的虛偽。在外頭睡午覺的貓咪也好可愛～ 強力推薦～💕😍 Loved the ambience, food and service here. Simple, but heartwarming in winter! Recommended!
Pay ¥800 for a landscape view of Umeda. There's UV light that makes white clothing/shoes glow. Cool stuff🖖🏻

venue.name: Umeda Sky Building (梅田スカイビル)

tip.text: Great and chewy freshly made udon here. Have it hot or cold. I tried the Tsukimi udon (月見うどん) with grated mountain yam and fresh raw egg yolk, which was good👌🏻

location.crossStreet: 天保山ハーバービレッジ3F
formattedAddress: 海岸通1-1 (天保山ハーバービレッジ3F)
大阪市港区, 大阪府

venue.name: 杵屋 天保山ハーバービレッジ3F店

tip.text: We didn't try their mains, but their desserts were great!
If you're in a big group, the tatami room offers a lot of privacy. The food was great, albeit a bit too salty to our taste. I had the pork katsu with grated radish (oroshi), served with Ponzu👍🏻

venue.name: とんかつ がんこ 奈良店

tip.text: 印度風的肉片豆腐咖哩鍋就別試了... 習慣吃咖喱的人會覺得根本沒什麼味道(不夠鹹)。唯一咖哩沾醬與印度煎餅還行。The Meat & Tofu Pot at Indian Fans stall is tasteless. Their curry sauce and chapatti are fine though👌🏻
Have their bread pudding with cranberries and maple syrup, topped with vanilla ice cream for dessert. Sweet and slightly salty in the right balance👌🏻 Their salad was a little too salty for our taste
P.S.: Yuzu Cheesecake and the lovely ambience. I will be back very soon👌🏻

formattedAddress: 3 Temasek Boulevard, Suntec City Tower 1, #01-444/445, The Art Space @ Suntec

tip.text: Don't get the Truffled Fries🙅🏻☝🏻️ Eggs Royale was good, but a tad stingy with the smoked salmon. Have your green tea latte while it's hot. You won't want a powdery layer to form above!
Overpriced and mediocre. Dislike the fact that the pan turned cold very quickly, leaving our food cold and hard. They serve plain water FOC, so don't be pressurised by the staffs to order drinks!☝🏻️
Light and moist cakes! Would recommend the Matcha Bliss and Rose Lychee (SG50!). Coffee wasn't sour👌🏻 and their Hot Chocolate needs to be less milky. Will be back to try more things!
Also, do try their Budae Jjigae (Army Stew). One of the better ones I've tried in Singapore☝🏻️ The small serving should feed 2-3 pax with a side order of their fried chicken😋
Lacklustre service, but I really love the tranquility of this place. Really awesome and juicy katsu pork cutlets here, don't skip it! 🙆🏼💕
Love the ambience when it's empty. Scenic view along Orchard Road if you're sitting outdoors👌🏻 Try their Truffle Yakiniku Don. P.S.: ONSEN EGG. Awesome combination, but needs to be more salty👍🏻
Always loved their food! Try their Penne with Spicy Pesto and Seafood. Prepare some Thai Tea Granita in case🔥😎 Loved their Avocado and Shrimp salad in Som Tum dressing too. Perfect👌🏻

tip.text: Come here for a spectacular night view of Bangkok. Cocktails? Not really.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10400

tip.text: Also had the Injeolmi Toast. Nothing spectacular either. Seems to contain margarine spread (a big no-no🙅🏼) instead of using salted butter. Don't get it!
Really, you'll have to try this place! Forget about the truffle fries and duck confit (too oily and too salty respectively). Have their Steak Frites and Or Lu Lu Sotong (calamari)! SUPERB👌🏻
A pretty nice place to chill out at. Indoor always seems to be fully reserved across all branches? Outdoor will be too hot😞 Rosé & Berries Sangria is too cute💕
The Roast Breakfast was of good standard, but wasn't filling enough for me.😞 Crab Cake Benedict was actually just average, sadly. I'll need to try more of their food the next time I'm back!

tip.text: Tried their signature English breakfast, which was very salty and not too inspiring. Probably ordered the wrong breakfast. Acidic coffee, which I personally dislike. BONUS: Spot the cute waiter!😏
Macaron choices limited when we went in the evening. Good tart base for bourbon tarte! BUT we bit into some plastic pieces for our fully edible "apple"?! Will be back next time, but no more "apple"😅

tip.text: Pleasant and quaint little space that sees Japanese ladies having their daily afternoon tea and small chats. Their scones (matcha!🍵) and apple cheesecake are delicious!😋

tip.text: Choices were limited when I went. Cakes look cute, but I don't get the hype? They have Gryphon tea here.

tip.text: Comfort food! They have dumpling soup, "chwee kueh", noodle soups, and thai style Yen Ta Fo😋 No exorbitant prices too😉

venue.name: Yaowaraj Food & Drink (เยาวราชโภชนา)

tip.text: Still thinking about the awesome duck confit I had here last night. So flavourful, tender and moist! My friend and I agreed that it's VERY good. Love the slightly sweet salad dressing! I'll be back💕
Awesome food! Efficient and pleasant staffs, though it may get VERY busy sometimes. Will be back again👍 (Note: No service charge and GST!)
Service is almost non-existent; bad management. Get your own table if they look busy. No physical menu, so check out the board at the counter and order there. Share with a few friends (gets cloying)!
Awesome Bak Kut Teh! Peppery, rich, fragrant... Meat is fall-off-bone tender. So so good! As good as the ones across the border. Maybe even better!👍 Soup refill please! (Order through their iPad!)

venue.name: Old Street Bak Kut Teh 老街肉骨茶

tip.text: Contrary to what some tips were saying, the service is so good! The girls were all very pleasant! As for the tart shells, it's not too hard as said, neither (coming from someone with braces!)💕
I also had their Niçoise Salad. Up to standard, but just a tad too salty. Would appreciate it better if the supposed kitchen and washroom didn't face each other...😔
Try their latte! Aromatic, so silky, and not very bitter even without any sugar👍 Price is definitely on the high side; wouldn't go out of my way to come back though!
Excellent cheerful waiting staffs. Watermelon Lemonade is cooling on a humid evening, and highly recommended by staffs. Do try their Lychee Cuban Mojito, if tropical fruit is your thing!🍹
